Paramedics are on scene on the N3 Barry Marais in Vosloorus following a multiple-vehicle collision. JOHANNESBURG - At least nine people died following a multiple vehicle collision on the N3 near the Barry Marais offramp on Monday. ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring said paramedics treated several people who sustained injuries ranging from minor to critical. It's understood some of the vehicles caught alight. READ: One critically injured in N3 accident Ekurhuleni EMS spokesperson William Ntladi said the cause of the crash is still under investigation but it is speculated to be as a result of smoke from a brushfire interfering with visibility on the road.